{"_id":"post-961d7431-e898-43fd-863e-a9dee7be8335","_type":"post","title":"Introducing Turtle Graphics For Python","slug":{"_type":"slug","current":"python-turtle"},"body":[{"_key":"bfea4a751d72","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Ever since the ","_key":"bfea4a751d720"},{"_type":"span","marks":["a14c76e83f17"],"text":"LOGO programming language","_key":"bfea4a751d721"},{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":" educators have been using ","_key":"bfea4a751d722"},{"_type":"span","marks":["70815263c02e"],"text":"Turtle Graphics","_key":"bfea4a751d723"},{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":" to demonstrate the power of programming to their students while making it fun and interesting.[](preview end)","_key":"bfea4a751d724"}],"markDefs":[{"_key":"a14c76e83f17","_type":"link","href":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Logo_programming_language"},{"_key":"70815263c02e","_type":"link","href":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Turtle_graphics"}],"_type":"block","style":"normal"},{"_key":"d9403ed24f85","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"In fact, my first real programming experience was when I was 6 years old learning LOGO at school. I learned how to program the turtle to draw a square and a triangle which I then put together to create a house. However, I was frustrated that I had to keep repeating the code to create a village made from multiple houses -- and that's how discovered loops! It's a natural way for children to learn programming. Here is an ","_key":"d9403ed24f850"},{"_type":"span","marks":["8549302d1c78"],"text":"example turtle graphic house","_key":"d9403ed24f851"},{"_type":"span","marks":[],"text":" in repl.it :)","_key":"d9403ed24f852"}],"markDefs":[{"_key":"8549302d1c78","_type":"link","href":"https://repl.it/DoYJ/1"}],"_type":"block","style":"normal"},{"_key":"83a7b736ff2c","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"83a7b736ff2c0","text":"","marks":[]}],"markDefs":[],"_type":"block","style":"normal"},{"_key":"3f001174a884","children":[{"_type":"span","marks":[]